+# C3 Retention
+
+status: proposed workshop values - needs human decision before Phase 1 Contract Spine authoring
+decision owner: Tech Lead
+approval authority: Legal + PM
+source inputs: Architecture Exit Criteria, Exit Criteria Operations Plan, D-7 idempotency TTL, D-10 audit storage, PRD Data Retention and Cleanup, Story 1.3 fixture ownership notes
+last reviewed: 2026-05-11
+open questions: Legal + PM must approve or revise the proposed durations before Story 1.6 consumes C3 values.
+
+## Decision
+
+The proposed MVP retention policy is metadata-only and tenant-scoped. The values below are concrete workshop inputs, not final legal commitments. Each row includes the downstream consumer that would be blocked if Legal + PM do not approve the value before Phase 1 entry.
+
+| Data class | Retention duration | Deletion, tombstone, or anonymization behavior | Cleanup trigger | Operational evidence | Provenance | Approval state | Tenant-isolation implication | Future consumer | Review date |
+|---|---:|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
+| Audit metadata | 7 years | Keep metadata-only audit records; anonymize user display aliases on tenant-deletion workflows while preserving correlation, category, timestamps, and outcome | Scheduled retention job plus tenant-deletion workflow | Audit projection retention report and sampled replay evidence | Architecture C3, D-10, PRD Data Retention and Cleanup | proposed workshop value; needs human decision for Legal + PM approval | Audit keys remain scoped by managed tenant ID; no payload, token, file content, or unauthorized resource existence is retained | Story 7.11 retention enforcement and Story 6.1 audit query endpoints | 2026-05-11 |
+| Workspace status | 400 days | Keep terminal status metadata for completed, failed, denied, retried, duplicate, and interrupted operations; tombstone task-local display labels after tenant deletion | Status compaction job after retention window | Workspace status projection age histogram and compaction summary | Architecture C3 and C6, PRD cleanup visibility | proposed workshop value; needs human decision for Legal + PM approval | Status records remain partitioned by tenant and folder; status lookup never crosses tenant scope | Story 4.9 workspace status and Story 6.6 diagnostic pages | 2026-05-11 |
+| Provider correlation IDs | 400 days | Retain provider request IDs, operation IDs, and upstream status classes only; do not retain tokens, repository contents, or provider payload bodies | Provider-diagnostics compaction tied to workspace status retention | Provider-correlation purge summary with redaction sentinel check | Architecture C3, provider readiness decisions, PRD failure visibility | proposed workshop value; needs human decision for Legal + PM approval | Correlation IDs are tenant-sensitive metadata and cannot be searched outside tenant authorization | Story 3.5 provider readiness diagnostics and Story 4.13 failure evidence | 2026-05-11 |
+| Read-model views | 400 days or until rebuilt from event streams, whichever is sooner | Rebuildable projections may be dropped and rebuilt; retained values must remain metadata-only | Projection rebuild, tenant-deletion workflow, or scheduled projection compaction | Projection watermark, rebuild manifest, and freshness metric | Architecture C3, C2 dependency, D-10 audit storage | proposed workshop value; needs human decision for Legal + PM approval | Projection keys include tenant scope; stale projection data must fail closed on tenant-access revocation | Story 2.7 lifecycle inspection and Story 6 operations console pages | 2026-05-11 |
+| Temporary working files | 7 days after terminal workspace state | Delete disposable working-copy files; retain only metadata evidence needed for status and audit | Workspace cleanup worker after commit, failure, cancellation, or lock expiry | Cleanup record with task ID, outcome category, and timestamp | Architecture C3, D-8 working-copy storage, PRD cleanup visibility | proposed workshop value; needs human decision for Legal + PM approval | Working paths are scoped under tenant, folder, and task IDs; cleanup evidence never includes file contents | Story 4.10 workspace cleanup status and Story 4.6 file mutation transport | 2026-05-11 |
+| Cleanup records | 400 days | Keep metadata-only cleanup attempts, failures, retryability, reason code, and correlation ID; anonymize human display aliases on tenant deletion | Retention compaction after cleanup record age crosses policy | Cleanup retry dashboard and audit sample | Architecture C3, PRD cleanup failure observability | proposed workshop value; needs human decision for Legal + PM approval | Cleanup evidence remains tenant-prefixed and does not reveal unauthorized repository existence | Story 4.10 cleanup status and Story 7.14 operations documentation | 2026-05-11 |
+| Folder metadata and soft-delete markers | Lifetime of tenant plus 400 days after tenant-deletion request enters approved retention workflow | Tombstone folder identity and hierarchy metadata; retain only audit-safe identifiers required for legal hold or audit replay | Folder archive, tenant deletion, or legal-hold workflow | Archive and deletion manifest with tenant-scoped counts | Architecture C3, PRD folder archive journey | proposed workshop value; needs human decision for Legal + PM approval | Folder IDs stay opaque; hierarchy paths are tenant-sensitive and not emitted in cross-tenant diagnostics | Story 2.8 archive folders and Story 7.11 tenant-deletion behavior | 2026-05-11 |
+| Auth claims copied into metadata | 400 days | Retain normalized `sub`, transformed tenant claim, and permission category only; anonymize display aliases where present | Audit/status compaction and tenant-deletion workflow | Claim-metadata retention sample with no raw token material | Architecture S-3, C3, PRD security and tenant isolation | proposed workshop value; needs human decision for Legal + PM approval | Payload tenant values are never authoritative; retained claims must trace to EventStore-transformed tenant context | Story 2.6 layered authorization and Story 7.2 OIDC configuration | 2026-05-11 |
+| Diagnostics and rejected-command records | 400 days | Retain canonical error category, correlation ID, retryability, client action, and bounded metadata; do not retain command payloads | Error-record compaction after retention window | Rejection corpus sample and redaction sentinel check | Architecture error catalog, C3, PRD failure visibility | proposed workshop value; needs human decision for Legal + PM approval | Denials must not reveal unauthorized resource existence or cross-tenant search results | Story 4.13 canonical errors and Story 5 cross-surface parity | 2026-05-11 |
+| Commit idempotency records | Same as audit metadata: 7 years | Persist commit operation IDs for the audit retention period; compact mutation-only idempotency records separately | Idempotency retention job keyed by `x-hexalith-idempotency-ttl-tier` | Idempotency TTL report comparing mutation and commit tiers | Architecture D-7 and C3 operations plan | proposed workshop value; needs human decision for Legal + PM approval | Commit replay stays tenant-scoped and returns the same logical result without exposing provider payloads | Story 1.6 Contract Spine extension vocabulary and Story 4.12 commit reconciliation | 2026-05-11 |
+
+## Rationale
+
+C3 is Phase-1-blocking because the Contract Spine must expose D-7 idempotency TTL semantics before client and parity work starts. The proposed durations keep audit and reconciliation evidence long enough to support operational review while keeping temporary working files short-lived because they are disposable caches, not authoritative state.
+
+No row invents a final legal policy. The proposed values are concrete enough for review, and every row names the authority gap that must close before Phase 1 uses the values as binding defaults.
+
+## Verification impact
+
+Verification must prove this artifact exists, contains no generic placeholders, contains only metadata-only examples, and maps each duration to a consuming future story or artifact. Later retention implementation must add tests for tenant-prefixed keys, deletion/tombstone behavior, audit replay, and commit idempotency TTL inheritance.
+
+## Deferred implementation
+
+This document does not add cleanup workers, projection compaction, tenant-deletion flows, audit endpoints, Dapr state configuration, OpenAPI fields, or idempotency code. Story 1.6 must not treat C3 as unblocked until Legal + PM approve or revise the proposed values.
