+# C4 Input Limits
+
+status: proposed workshop values - needs human decision before Phase 1 Contract Spine authoring
+decision owner: Architect
+approval authority: PM
+source inputs: Architecture Exit Criteria, Exit Criteria Operations Plan, PRD Performance and Query Bounds, Story 1.3 fixture ownership notes
+last reviewed: 2026-05-11
+open questions: PM must approve or revise the proposed MVP bounds before Story 1.6 writes OpenAPI schema limits.
+
+## Decision
+
+The proposed MVP input limits are global defaults. Later capacity calibration may revise them with evidence, but this artifact gives the Contract Spine author concrete bounded values and boundary semantics for Phase 1.
+
+| Limit | Value | Units and boundary semantics | Query families | Timeout or truncation behavior | OpenAPI field-mapping notes | Audit visibility | Provenance | Approval state | Future consumer | Review date |
+|---|---:|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|
+| Maximum requested paths | 100 | Inclusive count; applies to client input before authorization and path-policy checks | metadata lookup, bounded range, context query by path list | Exceeding the bound returns canonical `input_limit_exceeded`; no partial execution | Apply `maxItems: 100` to path arrays and `x-hexalith-limit-scope: request-path-count` | Audit includes requested count, rejected count, and canonical category; path values are excluded | Architecture C4 and PRD Performance and Query Bounds | proposed workshop value; needs human decision for PM approval | Story 1.6 Contract Spine schemas and Story 4.8 context-query authorization | 2026-05-11 |
+| Maximum tree entries returned | 2000 | Inclusive count after tenant authorization and path filtering | file tree and glob listing | Return partial metadata with `isTruncated = true` and no file contents | Apply `maxResultCount: 2000` extension metadata to tree response contracts | Audit includes result count and truncation flag; item names are tenant-sensitive and excluded from cross-tenant diagnostics | Architecture C4 and C8 query-family planning | proposed workshop value; needs human decision for PM approval | Story 1.9 context-query contract groups and Story 6.6 diagnostic pages | 2026-05-11 |
+| Maximum search or glob results | 500 | Inclusive count after authorization and path-policy filtering | search, glob, context query matching | Return partial metadata with `isTruncated = true`; clients must refine query for more | Apply `maxResultCount: 500` and `x-hexalith-truncation: partial-results` | Audit includes query family, result count, truncation flag, and limit tier; search text is excluded | Architecture C4 and PRD query bounds | proposed workshop value; needs human decision for PM approval | Story 1.9 context-query contract groups and Story 5 parity oracle | 2026-05-11 |
+| Maximum single bounded range bytes | 262144 | Inclusive byte count per file range after authorization and path-policy checks | bounded range read and small context snippets | Exceeding the bound returns canonical `input_limit_exceeded`; client may request a smaller range | Apply `maxBytes: 262144`, `maxLength: 262144`, or equivalent extension metadata to range contracts | Audit includes requested byte count and rejected/accepted outcome only | Architecture C4 and D-9 256KB inline boundary | proposed workshop value; needs human decision for PM approval | Story 1.9 file context contracts and Story 4.8 range queries | 2026-05-11 |
+| Maximum aggregate response bytes | 1048576 | Inclusive serialized response budget after authorization and filtering | tree, search, glob, metadata, bounded range, context query response payloads | If response budget is exceeded, return partial metadata when the family supports truncation; otherwise return `response_limit_exceeded` | Apply `maxBytes: 1048576` or `x-hexalith-response-budget-bytes: 1048576` | Audit includes response byte count and truncation/error category; response body is never logged | Architecture C4 and PRD performance target | proposed workshop value; needs human decision for PM approval | Story 1.6 OpenAPI extensions and Story 4.8 context query execution | 2026-05-11 |
+| Maximum query duration | 2 | Inclusive seconds of server-side execution budget after request validation and authorization start | all context-query families | Timeout returns canonical `query_timeout`; partial results only when the family already declares truncation support | Apply `x-hexalith-query-timeout-ms: 2000` and document canonical error mapping | Audit includes elapsed milliseconds, timeout flag, and correlation ID | Architecture C4 and NFR 2s context-query target | proposed workshop value; needs human decision for PM approval | Story 1.9 query contracts and Story 4.13 canonical errors | 2026-05-11 |
+| Timeout behavior | 2 | Seconds; timeout measured server-side and not extended by retries | all context-query families | No automatic retry inside the handler; client receives stable canonical failure or documented partial response | Apply error response mapping to Problem Details category `query_timeout` | Audit includes timeout category and retryable=false unless later contract states otherwise | Architecture C4 and error catalog | proposed workshop value; needs human decision for PM approval | Story 4.8 context queries and Story 5 CLI/MCP parity | 2026-05-11 |
+| Truncation behavior | 1 | One truncation flag per response; applies only after authorization/path filtering | file tree, search, glob, context-query response payloads | Partial metadata may be returned with `isTruncated = true`; file contents are never silently truncated | Apply `isTruncated`, `truncatedReason`, and limit extension metadata in future schemas | Audit includes limit name, configured limit, actual count/bytes, and truncation flag | Architecture C4 and operations-console diagnostic requirements | proposed workshop value; needs human decision for PM approval | Story 1.9 context-query schemas and Story 6.6 operator diagnostics | 2026-05-11 |
+| Included and excluded audit visibility | 0 | Numeric bound is not applicable; this row fixes audit field semantics | all context-query families | Included: query family, configured limit, actual count/bytes, elapsed time, truncation, canonical category, correlation ID. Excluded: raw query text, file content, path lists, unauthorized resource existence | Apply `x-hexalith-audit-metadata-keys` without adding payload fields | Audit is metadata-only and tenant-scoped | Architecture C4, S-6, and PRD Security and Tenant Isolation | proposed workshop value; needs human decision for PM approval | Story 1.6 audit metadata extension vocabulary and Story 7.6 redaction gates | 2026-05-11 |
+
+## Rationale
+
+The MVP should fail predictably before a query can become an unbounded tenant or repository scan. Bounds apply before or after authorization according to the table so implementers cannot search first and filter later. The values are conservative enough for early consumers while keeping C1 and C5 capacity calibration separate.
+
+The proposed rows are global MVP defaults. Tenant-tunable limits are deferred until release calibration has evidence and a configuration model.
+
+## Verification impact
+
+Verification must prove every numeric value has units, boundary semantics, provenance, approval state, a future consuming artifact, and a review date. Story 1.6 must carry these values into OpenAPI keywords or Hexalith extension metadata without creating per-tenant override files.
+
+## Deferred implementation
+
+This document does not create or edit OpenAPI, SDK generation, query handlers, middleware, rate limiters, tenant configuration, operations-console UI, or CI gates. PM approval remains the blocker before Contract Spine authoring treats these values as binding defaults.
